# Angular Architecture Guardrails

## Purpose
Ensure generated code follows this repository architecture and avoids context drift.

## Mandatory rules
- Use existing project architecture before introducing new patterns.
- For feature work, keep boundaries by layer:
  - `use-cases` can depend on `state` and `types`.
  - `state` can depend on `data-access` and `types`.
  - `data-access` can depend only on `types`.
  - `types` must not depend on other libs.
- Prefer imports through public aliases (`@oper/*`) instead of deep relative imports across projects.

## Angular patterns
- Prefer Angular Signals for local reactive state (`signal`, `computed`, `effect` where applicable).
- Prefer `@ngrx/signals` store pattern for feature state.
- Prefer typed Reactive Forms (`FormBuilder`, `FormGroup`, `FormControl`).
- Do not introduce template-driven forms (`ngModel`) in new code.
- Do not add `FormsModule` to implement new forms unless explicitly requested.

## Validation expectations
- After changes, run lint for affected projects.
- Preserve existing behavior and update tests when feature behavior changes.
